                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "6a0bf3cdfe7c0fc427c7b8ea9310f113",
                "text": "You must physically manipulate an item or make gestures to use an action with this trait. Creatures without a suitable appendage can\u2019t perform actions with this trait. Manipulate actions often trigger reactions.",
                "schema_version": 1.1
            },
            {
                "name": "Metal",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "180279e4a2e6fa2992daac7a77cb9a69",
                "text": "Effects with the metal trait conjure or manipulate metal. Those that manipulate metal have no effect in an area without metal. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of metal or have a connection to magical metal.  \n  \nThese planes consist of chaotic and shifting structures and oceans of metal. Metal planes tend to exist in a state of change and decay, leaving plentiful pockets of air for visitors to breathe or move within. Creatures unlucky enough to be entombed in the plane\u2019s substance risk suffocation if they can\u2019t phase through metal. Wood creatures find the lack of stability and soil on a metal plane disconcerting and often fail to thrive in such environments.",
                "schema_version": 1.1
            },
            {
                "name": "Morph",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 113,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 301",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 301",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 301,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "784b88e5dda46521a21f84f64481f464",
                "text": "Effects that slightly alter a creature's form have the morph trait. Any Strikes specifically granted by a morph effect are magical. You can be affected by multiple morph spells at once, but if you morph the same body part more than once, the second morph effect attempts to counteract the first (in the same manner as two polymorph effects, described in that trait).  \n  \nYour morph effects might also end if you are polymorphed and the polymorph effect invalidates or overrides your morph effect. The GM determines which morph effects can be used together and which can't.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "counteract",
                        "alt": "counteract",
                        "game-obj": "Rules",
                        "aonid": 371
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "polymorph",
                        "alt": "polymorph",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 127
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1
            }
        ],
